oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Association Between Ration Protein and Economic Efficiency of Milk Production on Ontario Dairy Farms
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lissemore, K.
Kelton, D.
Martin, S. W.
Godden, S.
Vonk Noordegraaf, A.
Edge, V. L.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: protein content
economic efficiency
milk production
milk income minus feed costs
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: An investigation of the association between the protein content of the ration and the economic efficiency of milk production indicates that increasing forage protein on Ontario dairy farms increases the daily milk income minus feed costs (IMFC).
